Installation - Unix:
--------------------

1.  Read the README to understand how snmptt works

2.  Copy snmptt to /sbin and ensure it is executable (chmod +x snmptt)

3.  Edit the options between OPTIONS START and OPTIONS END in snmptt

4.  Modify the NET-SNMP snmptrapd.conf file by adding the following line:

	traphandle default /sbin/snmptt/usr/bin/qpage -q 1 -C /etc/qpage.cf

	Note:  	It is possible to configure snmptrapd to execute snmptt based on 
		the trap received, but using the default option is preferred
		
5.  Start SNMPTRAPD using the command line:  SNMPTRAPD -On.  The -On is required 
    otherwise snmptt will NOT recognize the traps.



Installation - Windows:
-----------------------

1.  Read the README to understand how snmptt works

2.  Create the directory c:\snmp and copy snmptt to it

3.  Edit the options between OPTIONS START and OPTIONS END in snmptt

4.  Modify the NET-SNMP snmptrapd.conf file by adding the following line:

	traphandle default perl c:\snmp\snmptt

	Note:  	It is possible to configure snmptrapd to execute snmptt based on the
		trap received, but using the default option is preferred
		
5.  Start SNMPTRAPD using the command line:  SNMPTRAPD -On.  The -On is required 
    otherwise snmptt will NOT recognize the traps.



